#1 Metastatic rectal cancer with a history of resected liver metastasis
Prior to meeting with Mr. and Mrs. Padro, I have had the opportunity to review his past medical records, laboratory tests, and imaging studies.  I have also had the opportunity to review this case in its entirety with my collaborating provider, Dr. Hernandez, who is in agreement with this plan.  At this time, it is recommended that he proceed with radiation therapy.  In fact, he is scheduled for simulation tomorrow and then to initiate radiation on March 8, 2010.  At this time, recommending that he be treated with oral Xeloda therapy.  I am checking into the coverage from his insurance regarding this treatment modality.  If this is not covered well, would then proceed with infusional 5-FU.  In regard to follow-up, I have informed Mr. Padro he would then have a month off following radiation therapy and then return approximately at that time to discuss any further therapy.  At this time, Dr. Hernandez is recommending observation only.  Dr. Hernandez has also recommended that I counsel some of the other GI oncologists as to their recommendations.  We will be contacting patient with the information.
#2 Follow-up
Plan to see Mr. Padro back approximately two-weeks into the start of his radiation therapy or approximately the week of March 22, 2010.  He denies any further questions or concerns.  He has our telephone number to contact us should he have any further questions or concerns.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

